The chemical composition and functional groups of the membranes was characterized by XPS (Fig. 6
                        A) and FT-IR (Fig. 6B). The degree of network crosslinking (DNC) was calculated based on the surface element content (Table 2
                        ). The N content of M2-M6 was higher than that of M1 (6.47%), which also indicated the successful embedding of TpPa-1 CONs. In Table 2, with the addition amounts of TpPa-1 CONs increased, the DNC increased and the O/N decreased gradually. This is due to the fact that the –NH2 group in the TpPa-1 CONs reacted with the TMC to form covalent bonds (Fig. 2A), which increases the cross-linkage of the polyamide layer, thus keeping the rejection rate of the TpPa-1 CONs nanocomposite membrane at a high level [48]. In Fig. 5B, the -C-C stretching vibration of aryl group and -C-O stretching vibration of amide were at the range of 1560 cm−1–1700 cm−1, the increased peak intensity of -C-N at ∼1240 cm−1 illustrated the successful embedding of TpPa-1 CONs and the formation of β-ketoenamine linkages [49].
